  "chunk_index": 9,
  "summary": "Lorena and Eileen Bondell visit Jimmy Cessie to discuss the suspicious deaths of Gerry Wade and Ronnie. Lorena notes that Gerry never used sleeping pills, a fact Ronnie also found suspicious. After being woken by his servant, Stevens, Jimmy learns that two young women are waiting to see him. The first visitor is Lorraine, who is accompanied by Bondell.\n\nDuring their meeting, Lorraine reveals that Ronnie was shot and killed the previous day. Jimmy explains that on the day Gerry died, Ronnie had acted strangely and attempted to reveal information but claimed he had promised someone he would remain silent. Jimmy suspects Ronnie was secretly investigating Gerry's death and was killed to prevent him from uncovering the truth. The conversation centers on \"the seven-faced clock,\" which Jimmy concludes is likely the headquarters of a secret organization.\n\nLorena presents a letter left by Gerry, which Bondell had discovered. Lorena recalls seeing a different letter intended for Gerry that featured an inscription of seven clocks and contained a list of names and dates. She notes that Gerry had jokingly remarked on the lack of imagination in British criminals compared to organizations like the Mafia. Jimmy deduces that Gerry wanted Lorena to forget about the matter to protect her from the danger posed by this organization. Jimmy warns the group that pursuing the investigation will put them all in danger.",
